{{notability|date=August 2013}} A '''fail-silent system''' is a type of [[Computer system|system]] that either provides the correct [[Computer services|service]], or provides no service at all (becomes silent).<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.cs.newcastle.ac.uk/publications/articles/papers/146.pdf |title=Implementing fail-silent nodes for distributed systems |journal=IEEE Transactions on Computers |year=1996 |author1=F.V. Brasileiro |author2=P.D. Ezhilchelvan |author3=S.K. Shrivastava |author4=N.A. Speirs |author5=S. Tao |doi=10.1109/12.544479}}</ref>
