{{COI|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox website | name = Funzing | logo = Logo Funzing.png | logo_size = 250px | screenshot = | caption = | url = {{URL|http://www.funzing.com/}} | commercial = Yes | type = [[Social networking]] | language = [[English language|English]] | registration = | owner = | author = | launch date = {{start date and age|2014}} | current status = Active | revenue = | slogan = | alexa = }}
'''Funzing''' is an online [[sharing economy]] [[Online marketplace|marketplace]] that facilitates people to host and attend events and experiences in their leisure time based on their hobbies, passions or skills. Funzing was founded in Israel in 2014 by ''Avigur Zmora'', the former CEO of [[Playtech]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Former Playtech CEO launches Funzing - Globes English|url=http://www.globes.co.il/en/article-former-playtech-ceo-launches-funzing-1000965229|website=Globes|accessdate=9 March 2017|language=he}}</ref> Funzing is currently active in [[London]], [[Manchester]], [[Tel Aviv]] and [[Singapore]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Real People Show Off Their Talents Through Events With Funzing|url=http://londonist.com/2015/05/real-people-show-off-their-talents-through-events-with-funzing|website=Londonist|accessdate=9 March 2017|date=11 May 2015}}</ref> The online community marketplace promotes diversity in people’s [[Leisure time|free time activities]], experiences vary from [[supper clubs]], tours, workshops to one-off lectures and classes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Things To Do Today In London: Friday 24 February 2017|url=http://londonist.com/london/things-to-do/things-to-do-today-in-london-friday-24-february-2017|website=Londonist|accessdate=9 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Always Have Plans At Your Fingertips With This App|url=http://londonist.com/2016/03/download-the-funzing-app|website=Londonist|accessdate=9 March 2017|date=19 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Curtis|first1=Sophie|title=Now you can get PAID to play Pokemon Go - job listing appears for Pokemon Master|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tech/paid-play-pokemon-go-job-8607733|website=mirror|accessdate=9 March 2017|date=11 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pokémon GO: Here is how to make catching Pokémon a career|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/technology/social/pokemon-go-here-is-how-to-make-catching-pokemon-into-a-career-2976283/|website=The Indian Express|accessdate=9 March 2017|date=15 August 2016}}</ref>
== History == According to co-founder ''Yaron Saghiv'', the idea about the online sharing economy came out of several friends’ frustration at being bored by going to the same places every time they wanted to spend quality free time in a social setting. Thus, they devised the platform which allows anyone with creative potential to showcase their skills to the world while entertaining others and earning some money along the way.<ref>{{cite web|title=Company pays lady in S’pore S$1000 a month to organise an event every week, somehow this is good news {{!}} Mothership.SG|url=http://mothership.sg/2016/08/company-pays-lady-in-spore-s1000-a-month-to-organise-an-event-every-week-somehow-this-is-good-news/|website=mothership.sg|accessdate=9 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SafeCharge Enables Payments for Innovative Marketplace Funzing|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/safecharge-enables-payments-for-innovative-marketplace-funzing-2017-03-02|website=MarketWatch|accessdate=9 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SafeCharge enables payments for sharing economy marketplace Funzing|url=https://www.finextra.com/pressarticle/68277/safecharge-enables-payments-for-sharing-economy-marketplace-funzing|website=Finextra Research|accessdate=9 March 2017|language=en|date=2 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SafeCharge Provides Payment Tech For Funzing {{!}} PYMNTS.com|url=http://www.pymnts.com/digital-payments/2017/safecharge-provides-payment-technology-for-innovative-marketplace-funzing/|website=www.pymnts.com|accessdate=9 March 2017}}</ref> Funzing was founded in Israel in 2014. It was the brainchild of Avigur Zmora, former CEO of [[Playtech]], who went on to set up the company together with Eran Alon, Noa Moscati and Yaron Saghiv. The initial investment capital to start Funzing was raised from [[venture capital]] firm ''Inimiti'' and amounted to $1.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Innovation in Funding 2015-2016 competition entry: Funzing|url=https://www.theguardian.com/small-business-network/2015/sep/01/innovation-in-funding-2015-2016-funzing|website=The Guardian|accessdate=9 March 2017|date=1 September 2015}}</ref> Currently, there are over 2,000 registered hosts on the Funzing system, and more than 35,000 individuals have attended events as of June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Roue|first1=Lucy|title=Get creative as Funzing launches in Manchester|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/business/creative-funzing-launches-manchester-11414338|website=men|accessdate=9 March 2017|date=2 June 2016}}</ref>
